author: Adam Gartrell
title: Malcolm Turnbull's multimillion-dollar political donation to Liberal Party remains secret for another year
text:
Bomb squad called to Bourke Street Mall Bomb squad called to Bourke Street Mall 
Renewed fear hits Melbourne CBD as police quickly move frightened people away from Bourke Street Mall after a suspicious package was found. More videos Donations debate rolls on 
Former PM Tony Abbott has joined in the call to ban foreign and other donations to political parties. 
That absence suggests Mr Turnbull gave the money after June 30, which was just two days before polling day. Mr Turnbull's office has declined to comment. 
Mining businessman Paul Marks was the biggest donor to any party, personally giving $1.3 million to the Liberal Party in July 2015. It is believed to be the second biggest personal donation in Australian history, behind only Graeme Wood's $1.6 million 2010 donation to the Greens. SHARE
